		<item>
		<title>UIC Library receives grant to develop tools supporting student success</title>
		<link>https://today.uic.edu/uic-library-receives-grant-to-develop-tools-supporting-student-success/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Carlos Sadovi]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 18 Aug 2022 16:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Campus]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[student success]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[UIC Library]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://today.uic.edu/?p=134228</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The two-year project is a collaboration between the UIC Library and the library at Northern Illinois University ]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/2018-09-12fall-semester-campus-photos-photo-fan-wang-5"><img loading="lazy" width="590" height="393" src="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-590x393.jpg" alt="campus photos" class="wp-image-69168" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-590x393.jpg 590w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-387x258.jpg 387w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-768x512.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-1000x667.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-500x333.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA-300x200.jpg 300w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/20180912-IMG_4911AA.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" /></a><figcaption>The UIC Library is a recipient of a grant supporting student success. </figcaption></figure></div>



<p>The University of Illinois Chicago Library was awarded a $250,000 grant from the Institute of Museum and Library Services. </p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-large is-resized"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/jung-mi-scoulas-phdassistant-professor-and-assessment-coordina"><img loading="lazy" src="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-271x406.jpg" alt="Jung Mi Scoulas, PhD Assistant Professor and Assessment Coordinator University Library" class="wp-image-134834" width="142" height="213" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-271x406.jpg 271w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-172x258.jpg 172w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-500x750.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6-1000x1500.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Jung-Mi-Scoulas-PhD_4x6.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 142px) 100vw, 142px" /></a><figcaption>Jung Mi Scoulas, PhD </figcaption></figure></div>



<p>The grant aims to develop assessment tools that utilize information such as students’ academic engagement, psychological factors and their own perspectives of success to identify activities that can be promoted to students to support their academic achievement.</p>



<p>UIC&#8217;s award is one of 71 awards, totaling more than $21 million, issued in fiscal year 2022 to libraries and archives across the country through the Institute of Museum and Library Services National Leadership Grants for Libraries program and the Laura Bush 21st Century Librarian Program.</p>



<p>For this grant, UIC will conduct research to answer questions about student success that go beyond learning analytics and how library use plays a role in student success. The tools and research findings from this project will be disseminated to academic libraries to help them assess their impact on student success and to identify how libraries can better meet students’ needs.</p>



<p>The two-year project is a collaboration between the UIC Library and the library at Northern Illinois University – two institutions that serve underrepresented and first-generation students. </p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-large is-resized"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/sandra-de-groote"><img loading="lazy" src="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-271x406.jpg" alt="Sandra De Groote" class="wp-image-134835" width="140" height="210" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-271x406.jpg 271w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-172x258.jpg 172w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-500x750.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6-1000x1500.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Sandra-De-Groote_4x6.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 140px) 100vw, 140px" /></a><figcaption>Sandra De Groote</figcaption></figure></div>



<p>&#8220;We are grateful to have received an IMLS National Leadership Grant. With this funding, we have an opportunity to better understand specifics about how race, class and economic status impact our students as they pursue their educational goals. Our project is unique in that it considers students&#8217; actual lived experiences and asks the students themselves to define what success means to them. With this knowledge, we can individualize the services, resources and support we provide to better meet student needs and then share what we&#8217;ve learned with other academic libraries and institutions,” said Rhea Ballard-Thrower, UIC Dean of Libraries.</p>



<p>The principal investigator and project director is Jung Mi Scoulas, PhD and an assistant professor and assessment coordinator at the UIC Library. A co-principal investigator for the project is Sandra De Groote, professor and head of UIC’s assessment and scholarly communication department. NIU library faculty Nestor Osorio, head of reference and research, and Kimberly Shotick, student success librarian, will coordinate the study among NIU students.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft size-medium is-resized"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/institute-of-museum-and-library-services-logo-2"><img loading="lazy" src="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-387x258.jpg" alt="Institute of Museum and Library Services logo" class="wp-image-134107" width="294" height="196" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-387x258.jpg 387w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-590x393.jpg 590w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1.jpg 1800w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-1000x667.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-500x333.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/imls_logo_black_6x4-1-1320x880.jpg 1320w" sizes="(max-width: 294px) 100vw, 294px" /></a></figure></div>



<p><a href="https://www.imls.gov/grants/awarded/lg-252338-ols-22">View the full research project proposal</a> for grant number LG-252338-OLS-22.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.imls.gov/">The Institute of Museum and Library Services</a> is the primary source of federal support for the nation&#8217;s libraries and museums. The institute advances, supports and empowers America’s museums, libraries, and related organizations through grantmaking, research and policy development. Its vision is a nation where museums and libraries work together to transform the lives of individuals and communities. </p>


]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Media Advisory: Move-in Day 2022 </title>
		<link>https://today.uic.edu/media-advisory-move-in-day-2022/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Carlos Sadovi]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Aug 2022 14:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Campus]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Academic and Residential Complex]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Campus Housing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[residence halls]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://today.uic.edu/?p=134302</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[More than 3,000 students in total will live on campus in one of UIC’s eight residence halls]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/?attachment_id=116469"><img loading="lazy" width="590" height="393" src="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-590x393.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-116469" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-590x393.jpg 590w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-387x258.jpg 387w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-768x512.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382.jpg 1300w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-1000x667.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-500x333.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/081821_Move-in-Day_JC0382-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" /></a><figcaption>Incoming freshmen move into UIC in 2021. More than 3,000 students will live on campus this fall.</figcaption></figure></div>



<p>Hundreds of University of Illinois Chicago administrators, staff, student volunteers and student-athletes will welcome first-year students and help them move into residence halls for the fall 2022 semester.&nbsp;</p>



